        <hl1>On the Attack, Politely</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Senator Joseph I. Lieberman has a rare talent for making harsh attacks that do not come across as attacks. He has stepped up criticism of Gov. George W. Bush, but he often sounds less like a politician than like a neighbor sharing a troubling bit of gossip.</p>
        <p>Article, Page A12.</p>
